Finite vs. Countable
Question: Toss a coint till the first tail comes up. What is the probability that the number of tosses was odd?
Take the sample space the set of all countably infinite sequences: \[
\begin{aligned}
\Omega & = \{(w_1, w_2, w_3, ...): w_j \in \{H,T\}\} \\
& = \{w: N \rightarrow \{H, T\}\}
\end{aligned}
\]
Probability measures are countably additive
